<BLOCK1><TI>SUMMARY APPLICATION</TI>
<P>THE APPLICANT MAKES AN APPLICATION FOR:</P>
<P>1. an Order under 231.7 of the <EM>Income Tax Act</EM>, R.S.C. 1985, c. 1 (the &ldquo;<EM>Act</EM>&rdquo;) compelling the respondent to provide the applicant with the books, records and information specified in the requirement to provide documents or information that was issued to the respondent on September 16, 2016;</P>
<P>2. costs on this application; and</P>
<P>3. such further and other relief as this Court deems appropriate.</P>
<P>THE GROUND FOR THE APPLICATION ARE:</P>
<P>1. by requirement to provide documents or information dated September 16, 2016, the applicant requested pursuant to s. 231.1 (1) of the Act, that the respondent provide the applicant with specified books, records and information for purposes related to the administration and enforcement of the <EM>Act</EM>;</P>
<P>2. the respondent was required to provide such documents and information under s. 231.1(1) of the <EM>Act</EM>;</P>
<P>3. the respondent has failed to provide such documents and information;</P>
<P>4. the information and documents requested are not protected from disclosure by solicitor-client privilege, as defined in 232(1) of the <EM>Act</EM>; and</P>
<P>5. the applicant relies on s. 231.1(1), 231.7 and 232(1) of the <EM>Act</EM>, as well as on such further and other grounds as counsel may submit and the Court accept.</P>
<P>THE APPLICATION WILL BE SUPPORTED BY THE FOLLOWING MATERIAL</P>
<P>1. the affidavit of Saad Douab; and</P>
<P>2. such further material as counsel for the applicant may submit and this Honourable Court permits.</P>
