<BLOCK1><TI>AFFIDAVIT OF XUE LIN</TI>
<P><BOLD>I, Xue Lin,</BOLD> of the City of Shenzhen, in the Province of Guangdong, China, <BOLD>HEREBY MAKE OATH AND SAY:</BOLD></P>
<P>1. Where I express opinions in this Affidavit, those are founded on my experience, my discussions with my wife, Ming Wang, my daughter Lin Lin and CRA representatives.</P>
<P>2. Where I make statements in the context of this Affidavit that are not within my personal knowledge, I identify the source of the information and verily believe the information to be true.</P>
<P>3. I reside at XXXXXXXXXX</P>
<BLOCK2><TI><UNDER>Background</UNDER></TI>
<P>4. I was born in XXXXXXXXXX in Nanyang, in the province of Henan, in the People's Republic of China (&ldquo;China&rdquo;).</P>
<P>5. I received my undergraduate education in Henan University of Animal Husbandry and Economy and became a lecture instructor at the same University after graduation in 1983.</P>
<P>6. I married Min Wang in 1986 and had our only daughter Lin Lin in December 1987.</P>
<P>7. I pursued post-graduate studies at South China Agricultural University from 1992 to 1994 and obtained a master's degree in science majoring in poultry disease.</P>
<P>8. I started working in the field of pig farming in a public company, Shenzhen Kondral (group) Co. LTD, from 1994 to 2012 in Shenzhen, Guangdong, China, and worked my way up to the position of Vice-President of the company overseeing the entire agriculture sector.</P>
<P>9. Prior to entering Canada, I received landed immigrant status in Canada.</P>
<P>10. In May of 2004, my wife, Min Wang, made an application for permanent residence in China on behalf of myself, herself and my daughter.</P>
<P>11. I came to Canada as a landed immigrant on May 26, 2005 with my wife and daughter.</P>
<P>12. In 2005, I immigrated with my family to Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada.</P>
<P>13. My intention at the time was not to remain in Canada.</P>
<P>14. I realized that in order to support my wife and daughter's life in Canada, I needed to continue my career in China, so I flew back to China two weeks after landing in Canada in July 2005.</P>
<P>15. I continued paying taxes to the Chinese authorities as a Chinese resident, attached please see
<P1><BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> Certificate of Chinese Fiscal Resident for the taxation years 2005 to 2009 and</P1>
<P1><BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> Certificate of Chinese Fiscal Resident for the taxation years 2010 to 2015.</P1></P>
<P>16. In September 2005, I paid a short visit to Canada for the closing of the house in Guelph, Ontario, and flew back to China for work subsequently.</P>
<P>17. Since landing Canada, my visits to Canada have been of a temporary nature and were predominantly for recreational purposes, mostly during the holiday season.</P>
<P>18. I have a significant number of relatives living in China, including my brother.</P>
